quran[25]{c,v,t}:
  55,1,The Compassionate
  55,2,Has taught the Quran
  55,3,He created man
  55,4,And taught him clear expression
  55,5,The sun and the moon move according to plan
  55,6,And the stars and the trees prostrate themselves
  55,7,"And the sky, He raised; and He set up the balance"
  55,8,So do not transgress in the balance
  55,9,"But maintain the weights with justice, and do not violate the balance"
  55,10,And the earth; He set up for the creatures
  55,11,"In it are fruits, and palms in clusters"
  55,12,"And grains in the blades, and fragrant plants"
  55,13,So which of your Lord’s marvels will you deny
  55,14,"He created man from hard clay, like bricks"
  55,15,And created the jinn from a fusion of fire
  55,16,So which of your Lord’s marvels will you deny
  55,17,Lord of the two Easts and Lord of the two Wests
  55,18,So which of your Lord’s marvels will you deny
  55,19,"He merged the two seas, converging together"
  55,20,"Between them is a barrier, which they do not overrun"
  55,21,So which of your Lord’s marvels will you deny
  55,22,From them emerge pearls and coral
  55,23,So which of your Lord’s marvels will you deny
  55,24,"His are the ships, raised above the sea like landmarks"
  55,25,So which of your Lord’s marvels will you deny